==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warp knitting
<hw>Warp knitting</hw>. <def>A kind of knitting in which a number of
threads are interchained each with one or more contiguous threads on
either side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warproof</ent>⟦br⟧
